import {Navbar, Container, Nav, Image, Row, Col} from 'react-bootstrap';
import {Link} from 'react-router-dom';

function NavegationBar(){
    return(
        <Navbar bg="dark" expand="lg" variant='dark'>
            <Container>
                <Row>
                    <Col>
                        <Image src={require('../images/TazasFondoNegro.png')} className="img-fluid" width="60%" alt="taza"></Image>
                    </Col>
                    <Col className=" my-5 py-5">
                        <Navbar.Brand href="#home">Rec Sublime</Navbar.Brand>
                    </Col>
                    <Col>
                    <Navbar.Toggle aria-controls="basic-navbar-nav" />
                    <Navbar.Collapse id="basic-navbar-nav"> 
                        <Nav className="me-auto">
                            <Nav.Link href="#home" className="fs-5 mx-5">Home</Nav.Link>
                            <Nav.Link href="https://www.instagram.com/rec_sublime_/?hl=es-la" target="_blank" className="fs-5 mx-2">Instagram</Nav.Link>
                            <Nav.Link href="#home" className="fs-5 mx-2">About</Nav.Link>
                            <Nav.Link href="#home" className="fs-5 mx-2">Dise√±os</Nav.Link>
                            <Nav.Link href="#home" className="fs-5 mx-2">Contacto</Nav.Link>
                        </Nav>
                    </Navbar.Collapse>
                    </Col>
                </Row>
            </Container>
        </Navbar>
    );
}

export default NavegationBar;
